@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{browse-url-extras.el} extends Emacs' built-in @samp{browse-url} library with fine-grained control over which browser opens which URLs. By default, Emacs sends all URLs to the same browser function, but many users prefer to open certain domains in their system browser or in Firefox while keeping everything else in EWW@. This package makes that easy by reading domain lists from plain text files and configuring @code{browse-url-handlers} accordingly.

The package depends on @samp{browse-url}, @samp{eww}, @samp{paths}, @samp{f}, and @samp{s}.

The main capabilities are:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Per-domain browser routing.} Maintaining lists of domains that should open in the default system browser or in Firefox, loaded from configuration files (@ref{Browser routing}).
@item
@strong{Interactive domain management.} Adding the current page's domain to an external browser list with a single command (@ref{Adding domains}).
@item
@strong{External browsing.} Opening the current EWW or xwidget-webkit URL in an external browser, or opening URLs in the background (@ref{External browsing}).
@end itemize

@node User options
@chapter User options

@menu
* @code{browse-url-extras-browse-url-default-file}::
* @code{browse-url-extras-browse-url-firefox-file}::
@end menu

@node @code{browse-url-extras-browse-url-default-file}
@section @code{browse-url-extras-browse-url-default-file}

@vindex browse-url-extras-browse-url-default-file
The user option @code{browse-url-extras-browse-url-default-file} specifies the path to a plain text file listing domains (one per line) that should be opened with the system's default browser via @code{browse-url-default-browser}. When you encounter a domain that EWW handles poorly, you can add it to this file.

The default value points to @samp{etc/browse-url-default.txt} in the Emacs configuration directory (via @code{paths-dir-dotemacs}). The type is a file path.

@node @code{browse-url-extras-browse-url-firefox-file}
@section @code{browse-url-extras-browse-url-firefox-file}

@vindex browse-url-extras-browse-url-firefox-file
The user option @code{browse-url-extras-browse-url-firefox-file} specifies the path to a plain text file listing domains that should be opened specifically in Firefox via @code{browse-url-firefox}. This is useful for domains that require Firefox-specific features or extensions.

The default value points to @samp{etc/browse-url-firefox.txt} in the Emacs configuration directory. The type is a file path.

